m margin-small"><div itemprop=3D"text" class=3D"text-rich-text w-richtext">=
<p>Recursion involves a function calling itself to solve smaller sub-proble=
ms of the same type as the larger problem. In TSP, recursion is used in met=
hods like the "Divide and Conquer" strategy, breaking down the problem into=
 smaller, manageable subsets, which can be particularly useful in dynamic p=
rogramming solutions. It reduces redundancy and computation time, making th=
e problem more manageable.</p></div></div></div></div><div itemprop=3D"main=
Entity" itemtype=3D"https://schema.org/Question" itemscope=3D"itemscope" ro=
